on. His accessible book proposes a new way of confronting the unknown-one grounded in the calculation of risk. Declaring the classical right-left divide to be redundant, Innerarity presents his hopes for a renewed democracy and a politics that would find convincing ways to mediate between the priorities of the present, the heritage of the past, and the challenges that lie ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aFuture, ThexPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aSocial prediction. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aKingery, Sandra08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478221040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804782210423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804782210.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles